    <!-- Chosen Palette: "Journalistic Evolution" - Starts with Ink Black (#2D3748) and Paper White (#FDFBF7) for the vintage era, transitioning to Digital Blue (#3182CE) and Alert Red (#E53E3E) for the modern era. -->
    
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: 
         1. Hero: "The De-Evolution". A strong visual statement setting the premise that job ads have gotten worse.
         2. The Gold Standard (1914): Visualizing Shackleton's ad to demonstrate brevity and honesty (Cost per line era).
         3. Timeline of Disruption: Vertical interactive timeline scrolling through history (Referrals -> Print -> Internet).
         4. The Digital Pivot (The Problem): Interactive section explaining how "Unlimited Space" (Flat Fee) led to "Lazy Content" (Legal Descriptions).
         5. The Data Explosion: Chart showing the rise of job boards vs. the decline in ad quality.
         6. The Conflict: A side-by-side comparison of "Job Description" (Legal) vs. "Job Ad" (Marketing).
         7. Conclusion: Call to action to return to marketing principles.
    -->

    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices:
         1. Shackleton's Ad (Styled HTML Box): Goal -> Demonstrate "Succinct Honesty". Method -> CSS styled box resembling a broadside. Justification -> Visual storytelling of the "Best Ad Ever".
         2. Job Board Explosion (Line Chart): Goal -> Show scale. Method -> Chart.js. Justification -> Visualizes the massive jump from 1 board (Monster) to 100,000+.
         3. Length vs. Effectiveness (Scatter/Bubble): Goal -> Correlate pricing models with ad length. Method -> Chart.js. Justification -> Shows the "Flat Fee" effect on content bloat.
         4. Timeline (Vertical Layout): Goal -> History. Method -> HTML/Tailwind Grid. Justification -> Linear narrative from 3000BC to today.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
