                <h3 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6 text-yellow-500">1914: The "Perfect" Ad</h3>
                <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6 text-gray-300">
                    Before the internet, ads were priced <strong>by the line</strong>. Every word cost money. This forced recruiters to be honest, succinct, and compelling.
                </p>
                <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300">
                    Ernest Shackleton's ad for his Antarctic expedition is legendary. It didn't list "requirements" or "compliance." It sold a <strong>journey</strong>.
