                </div>

                <!-- Explanation Text -->
                <div class="space-y-6">
                    <div class="p-6 bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 rounded shadow-sm">
                        <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-2">The Pricing Shift</h4>
                        <p class="text-gray-700">
                            <strong>Old Way:</strong> Price per line. <br>
                            <span class="text-sm italic">Result: Brief, punchy, marketing-focused ads.</span>
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">
                            <strong>New Way:</strong> Flat fee / Unlimited text. <br>
                            <span class="text-sm italic">Result: Recruiters copy-pasted 3-page internal legal descriptions.</span>
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="p-6 bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 rounded shadow-sm">
                        <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-900 mb-2">The Content Crisis</h4>
                        <p class="text-gray-700">
                            Instead of writing advertisements, we started posting <strong>Job Descriptions</strong>—internal legal documents meant for evaluation, not attraction.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 4: INTERACTIVE COMPARISON -->
